com.github.dm.jrt.stream

Class AbstractStreamBuilder<IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dm.jrt.core.routine.TemplateRoutine<IN,OUT>
      • com.github.dm.jrt.core.builder.AbstractRoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>
        • com.github.dm.jrt.stream.AbstractStreamBuilder<IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    IN - the input data type.
    OUT - the output data type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>, InvocationConfigurable<RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>>, InvocationConfiguration.Configurable<RoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>>, Routine<IN,OUT>, StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>

    public abstract class AbstractStreamBuilder<IN,OUT>
extends AbstractRoutineBuilder<IN,OUT>
implements StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>
    Abstract implementation of a stream routine builder.

    This class provides a default implementation of all the stream builder features. The inheriting class just needs to create routine and configuration instances when required.

    Created by davide-maestroni on 07/01/2016.

      • immediate

        @NotNull
public StreamBuilder<IN,OUT> immediate()
        Description copied from interface: StreamBuilder
        Modifies the stream configuration, so that the concatenated routines will be invoked in asynchronous mode employing the shared immediate runner.
        Note, however, that the runner will still be overridden by the configured current one.

        Unlike the default synchronous runner, the employed one makes so that each routine in the chain is passed any input as soon as it is produced by the previous one. Such behavior decreases memory demands at the expense of a deeper stack of calls. In fact, the default synchronous runner breaks up routine calls so to perform them in a loop. The main drawback of the latter approach is that all input data might be accumulated before actually being processed by the next routine invocation.

        Specified by:
        immediate in interface StreamBuilder<IN,OUT>
        Returns:
        this builder.
        See Also:
        Runners.immediateRunner()
